---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <section style="padding-top: 60px; border-bottom: none;">
    <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
        <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ सत्यम् शिवम् सुन्दरम् ॥</span>
        <span class="tag">About</span>
        <h1>About <span class="highlight">LucentHindu</span></h1>
        <p class="lead" style="max-width: 650px;">
            Understanding who someone is requires more than a biography...
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Who I Am</h2>
            <p>My name is Aman. I am an independent systems thinker, researcher, and builder.</p>
            <p>My work sits at the intersection of digital presence, information architecture, knowledge systems, and operational design. I am interested in understanding how things work—whether those things are technologies, organizations, economies, ideas, or human behavior.</p>
            <p>Rather than focusing on isolated tactics, I prefer to work from foundations. I am drawn to first principles, recurring patterns, and structures that remain useful across time.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What I Do</h2>
            <p>Today, I help people and organizations build clearer, more effective digital presence, knowledge, and operational systems.</p>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Digital Presence Strategy</li>
                <li>Website & Information Architecture</li>
                <li>Content System Design</li>
                <li>Knowledge Management Infrastructure</li>
                <li>Workflow Optimization & Practical Automation</li>
                <li>Independent Research</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>How I Think</h2>
            <p>A few ideas shape how I approach work:</p>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Understanding before action</li>
                <li>Systems before tactics</li>
                <li>Clarity before complexity</li>
                <li>Long-term thinking over short-term optimization</li>
                <li>Useful over impressive</li>
                <li>Truth over convenience</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">How I Operate</h2>
            <p>Over time, I've found that most decisions become easier when guided by a small set of principles.</p>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Understanding Before Action</strong> — Before asking what to do, I try to understand what is happening.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Systems Over Tactics</strong> — Tactics change. Systems endure.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Clarity Over Complexity</strong> — If an idea cannot be explained clearly, there is usually more work to do.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Truth Over Convenience</strong> — Useful decisions require an honest view of reality.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Useful Over Impressive</strong> — I prioritize usefulness over appearance and outcomes over signals.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Long-Term Over Short-Term</strong> — I prefer decisions that remain useful years later.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Build To Understand</strong> — Ideas become clearer when tested against reality.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Everything Is Connected</strong> — Technology, psychology, economics, information, and institutions constantly influence one another.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Common Questions</h2>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">What is LucentHindu?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">LucentHindu is my long-term project. A place to organize ideas, document observations, build systems, publish resources, and explore questions related to reality, knowledge, technology, learning, and human life.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Why the name LucentHindu?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">Lucent represents clarity, learning, and understanding. Hindu reflects civilizational continuity, cultural context, and the transmission of knowledge across generations.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Do you have a degree?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">My learning has largely been self-directed through work experience, experimentation, books, observation, and independent study.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">What topics interest you?</h3>
                    <ul class="structural">
                        <li>Reality and first principles</li>
                        <li>Learning and knowledge</li>
                        <li>Systems thinking</li>
                        <li>Technology and AI</li>
                        <li>Human behavior</li>
                        <li>Information architecture</li>
                        <li>Institutions and society</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">What are you trying to accomplish?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">At the highest level: To better understand how things work. And to help make that understanding more accessible, organized, and useful.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">My Journey</h2>
                <p>The ideas on this site did not emerge all at once. They developed through years of observation, experimentation, work, failure, recovery, and self-directed learning.</p>
                <a href="/my-journey" class="btn" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">Read My Journey →</a>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">Work With Aman</h2>
                <p>Every engagement begins with understanding. Before recommendations, implementation, or optimization, I start by examining the system itself.</p>
                <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">Request a Systems Audit →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>